> Entertainment Vegas illusionist Criss Angel cancels shows to visit ill son FILE - In this June 22, 2011 file photo, Criss Angel appears on the red carpet before the 2011 NHL Awards, in Las Vegas. The Las Vegas magician, Angel, who stars in "Criss Angel BeLIEve" by Cirque Du Soleil at the Luxor casino-hotel, says he's canceling shows for the first time in seven years to visit his young son who was recently diagnosed with leukemia. A statement released Friday, Oct. 23, 2015, said Angel was canceling his shows beginning that night through Nov. 1 to be with his nearly 2-year-old son, Johnny Crisstopher Sarantakos, in Australia. (AP Photo/Julie Jacobson, File) 
